5|$|WASP-13 {{is a star}} in the Lynx constellation. The star is similar, {{in terms}} of {{metallicity}} and mass, to the Sun, although <b>it</b> <b>is</b> <b>hotter</b> <b>and</b> most likely older. The star was first observed in 1997, according to the SIMBAD database, and was targeted by SuperWASP after the star was observed by one of the SuperWASP telescopes beginning in 2006. Follow-up observations on the star led to the discovery of planet WASP-13b in 2008; the discovery paper was published in 2009.|$|R
